Argv parsing and report rendering for the ctx-verify checkpoint binary — the CLI surface that drives `checks::run_selected` and formats the resulting `Report` for humans or machines.

Two output modes over the same `Report`: default terse render (single `pass` line, or one `FAIL:`/`ERROR:`/`SKIP:` block per non-passing check with diagnostics clipped to `MAX_MSG` (100 chars) and capped by `--max-diagnostics`), or `--json` for the full `serde_json` machine contract consumed by ctx-run/CI. A skipped check is never silently dropped — it renders a `SKIP:` block and forces `report.status != Pass`, i.e. the gate fails closed.

`CONTRACT` is a load-bearing string constant: it's the single source of truth for the generated tool-contract block in `CLAUDE.md`/`README.md`, and the repo's own `contracts` battery check fails if that doc block drifts from this exact string — editing CONTRACT's wording requires regenerating those docs.

`Cli` fields map directly to check selection: `package` scopes cargo-based checks only (no module-level scoping concept), `checks` (comma-delimited) restricts to named checks instead of the full default gate, `json` switches render modes.

Key function: `pub fn run<R: Runner, W: Write>(runner: &R, cli: &Cli, out: &mut W) -> Result<bool, CheckError>` — returns `true` only if every selected check ran and passed; writes either JSON or terse output to `out`. Errors are `CheckError::Encode` (serialization) or `CheckError::Write` (I/O).

`render_terse`/`render_check` build the terse format: diagnostics are locator-aligned (`file:line`, padded to the widest locator in the block) then `lint: message`, with a `… +N more` tail when the list was truncated. `locator()` degrades to `"-"` when file is empty, or bare filename when line is 0.